Title: Odds Ratio Estimation in Bernoulli Smoothing Spline ANOVA Models  
Author: Yuedong Wang 
Keyword: Key Words: bias correction; bootstrap; odds ratio; smoothing spline ANOVA.  
Date: September 1, 1996  
Affiliation: Department of Biostatistics, University of Michigan  
Abstract: Wahba et al (1995) introduced Smoothing Spline ANalysis of VAriance (SS ANOVA) method for data from exponential families. In this paper, we estimate the odds ratios based on a SS ANOVA model for binary data and construct Bayesian confidence intervals. We show the calculation using a real data set from Wisconsin Epidemiological Study of Diabetic Retinopathy. We conduct simulations to evaluate the performance of these estimates and their Bayesian confidence intervals. Our simulations suggest that the odds ratio estimates are quite reasonable in general but may be biased towards unity when comparing estimates at peaks with those in valleys. A bootstrap procedure is proposed to correct possible biases and it works very well in our simulation. 
